1
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:37,340
There's a nurse at our military hospital

2
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,479
Tang Ju'er

3
00:01:40,479 --> 00:01:42,600
who's about the same age as Ye Biying

4
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:45,800
and might know something about the situation.

5
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:46,680
Indeed.

6
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:50,640
Are you referring to Tang Bingchen's daughter?

7
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:53,330
They probably know each other.

8
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:56,920
Telegraph room.

9
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,780
Send a telegram to Inoue Kamakura

10
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:03,240
telling him to mind his own business.

11
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:04,960
That colonel

12
00:02:04,960 --> 00:02:08,090
carries a personal letter from His Majesty the Emperor.

13
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:09,280
Someone of this importance

14
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,560
is better left alone.

15
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,560
Did you hear me?

16
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:19,480
Has my father sent a reply?

17
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:20,640
Yes, he has.

18
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:22,600
What did he say?

19
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:25,880
Mr. Inoue Akira says that imperial investigator

20
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:28,480
carries a personal letter from His Majesty the Emperor.

21
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:33,440
You'd better stay away from someone like him.

22
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:12,000
You can't do this.

23
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Are you really sanding the propeller with sandpaper?

24
00:03:15,360 --> 00:03:17,020
Do you want to try doing my job?

25
00:03:17,079 --> 00:03:19,240
I work three shifts a day.

26
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,800
There are hundreds of planes waiting for maintenance.

27
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,440
You're lucky I can fix yours

28
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:23,440
right now.

29
00:03:23,440 --> 00:03:24,640
Sir,

30
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:25,800
we mean no disrespect.

31
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:26,920
We've shown you

32
00:03:26,920 --> 00:03:27,760
General Arnold's orders.

33
00:03:27,760 --> 00:03:30,690
These planes need to be finished as soon as possible.

34
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:33,600
Could you please stop?

35
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:34,560
Do you realize

36
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,680
we're flying across the Pacific Ocean?

37
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,280
If you keep scraping with sandpaper,

38
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:40,480
the salt will cause the prop tips to curl up.

39
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:41,640
The Pacific.

40
00:03:41,640 --> 00:03:42,920
Finally someone tells me.

41
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,800
Where are these things going?

42
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:47,079
None of your business.

43
00:03:48,120 --> 00:03:48,880
Listen.

44
00:03:49,760 --> 00:03:52,360
If the commander really wants to do this,

45
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:54,280
I might have just the solution you're looking for.

46
00:03:54,280 --> 00:03:57,200
Modifying these planes.

47
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,120
But right now,

48
00:03:58,120 --> 00:03:59,560
my job is to

49
00:03:59,600 --> 00:04:01,960
do all this pointless work.

50
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:04,400
Fine.

51
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,920
Look at the scratches you made on the propeller.

52
00:04:06,920 --> 00:04:08,720
Apply some oil and smooth it out.

53
00:04:09,120 --> 00:04:09,580
Thanks.

54
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,240
Wake up, boys!

55
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,240
We're moving out.

56
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:46,800
March 28, 1942.

57
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:48,880
Doolittle Bomber Squadron

58
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:52,000
transferred to Sacramento for training.

59
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:15,560
Dr. Ozu

60
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:17,920
Private Kaixin,

61
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:21,600
it seems worse than yesterday.

62
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:23,420
Do you want to check it out?

63
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:26,360
Got it.

64
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,480
Tang Ju'er

65
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:24,520
What are you doing?

66
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:33,720
Let's go.

67
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,560
We're going to the comfort station.

68
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:42,920
Wait. I'll take you there.

69
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,040
I heard you've been looking for this book.

70
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:56,159
I specially asked my friend in Shanghai to find it.

71
00:06:56,159 --> 00:06:58,490
I brought it back hoping you would like it.

72
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,480
I've been looking for this book.

73
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,000
Thank you so much.

74
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,290
Have you read this book?

75
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,420
Yes, I have.

76
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:08,780
What do you think of it?

77
00:07:09,600 --> 00:07:11,200
This amazing American author

78
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,880
when writing this book in 1921

79
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:16,640
already predicted

80
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:18,560
that Japan would from the North Pacific

81
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,320
launch a surprise attack on Pearl Harbor.

82
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,520
Admiral Yamamoto Isoroku

83
00:07:21,520 --> 00:07:22,600
when he was a military attaché in America

84
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:25,800
I believe before he made this decision

85
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:27,760
Everyone must have read this book.

86
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:29,640
Colonel,

87
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:31,880
I'm convinced by you.

88
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:34,720
You're a man of wisdom close to the Emperor.

89
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,520
You've always been able to grasp

90
00:07:35,520 --> 00:07:37,780
the pulse of those generals' decisions.

91
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:41,560
I always have people find books for me afterwards,

92
00:07:41,560 --> 00:07:43,200
so I can only serve as a Lieutenant General out here.

93
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,840
I'm just a Colonel now.

94
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:45,920
No, no, no.

95
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:47,840
You will become a general.

96
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,540
You flatter me.

97
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:51,000
By the way,

98
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,080
Commander,

99
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:54,540
there's something I'd like to ask of you.

100
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:55,440
What is it?

101
00:07:57,159 --> 00:07:58,280
I've been ordered

102
00:07:58,280 --> 00:08:00,840
to investigate General Minoo Tsunaki's plane crash.

103
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:01,760
On the island,

104
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,320
I need a unit to assist me.

105
00:08:04,080 --> 00:08:05,160
The Special Police Unit

106
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,240
has very close ties

107
00:08:06,240 --> 00:08:07,360
with the Shanghai garrison.

108
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:09,320
So they can't be fully trusted.

109
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:12,560
General Tsunaki was previously in the Navy,

110
00:08:12,560 --> 00:08:13,560
so I hope you

111
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:15,880
can assign a unit from the Navy

112
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:17,600
to assist me with my work.

113
00:08:17,800 --> 00:08:19,920
The officers don't need to be high-ranking,

114
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:20,800
but preferably this unit

115
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,160
should avoid having members of the Southern Expansion Doctrine

116
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:24,220
or the Northern Expansion Doctrine.

117
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:25,760
Colonel,

118
00:08:26,680 --> 00:08:27,760
don't take those

119
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:29,440
Special Police Unit fellows seriously.

120
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,000
They're just a bunch of watchdogs

121
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,600
who bark at whoever comes in.

122
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:34,919
In my Marine Corps,

123
00:08:34,919 --> 00:08:36,840
there's an anti-aircraft artillery company.

124
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:37,880
Their main duty is

125
00:08:37,880 --> 00:08:39,679
to guard the ports and airports.

126
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:42,280
The Chinese forces have no air superiority,

127
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:43,940
so they haven't had much to do.

128
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,800
Except for those on standby duty,

129
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,660
you can deploy this unit anytime.

130
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:48,840
Excellent.

131
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:51,240
Then tomorrow I'll establish

132
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:54,240
my investigation headquarters at the anti-aircraft company.

133
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,520
Let Adjutant Sakamoto arrange your accommodations first.

134
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:57,280
Tomorrow,

135
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,200
I'll notify all department heads at the headquarters

136
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:00,280
to hold a welcome dinner for you.

137
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,400
The commander of the anti-aircraft company

138
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:03,160
is Lieutenant Akiyokawa Ken.

139
00:09:03,160 --> 00:09:04,480
I'll have him come to meet you.

140
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,320
Thank you.

141
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:22,920
Xiao Zhu.

142
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,280
Is the examination over?

143
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:26,860
Not yet.

144
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:28,240
Come over here,

145
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,370
I need to talk to you.

146
00:09:30,520 --> 00:09:31,160
Hurry up.

147
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:36,020
Bring the medical kit.

148
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:01,240
Who did this?

149
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:10,560
Come here,

150
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:12,480
check her condition.

151
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:30,340
You didn't use any inappropriate methods, did you?

152
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:32,880
I swear

153
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:34,240
Absolutely not.

154
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,840
Then why did Ye Degong refuse?

155
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:41,440
Sir.

156
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:43,960
If I may be so bold,

157
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:47,240
aren't we being too polite to these people?

158
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,560
Are you questioning me?

159
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,010
I wouldn't dare.

160
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:57,200
Let me tell you again.

161
00:10:58,320 --> 00:11:01,050
The key to governance lies in thought and spirit.

162
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,440
Instead of physical torture.

163
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:06,880
Ye Degong is the tribal chief of this island.

164
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:08,360
If we conquer him,

165
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:10,580
we conquer the entire Sanzao Island.

166
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:11,930
Understood.

167
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:21,720
What do you think about the newly arrived Major?

168
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,120
Well...

169
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:31,800
What I've been worried about has finally happened.

170
00:11:33,040 --> 00:11:34,440
General, you mean...

171
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,240
The plane crash of General Minao Ōsumi last year

172
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:39,440
caused quite a stir

173
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,360
and alarmed the Emperor.

174
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:44,360
Due to Prime Minister Fumimaro Konoe's resignation,

175
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:47,060
the investigation was temporarily suspended.

176
00:11:47,160 --> 00:11:50,360
Unexpectedly, they've now reopened the investigation.

177
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:51,600
Could it be that

178
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:55,240
the Major came here for this matter?

179
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:57,970
He not only wants to clarify

180
00:11:58,320 --> 00:12:00,720
the real cause of General Ōsumi's accident,

181
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,580
but also to find

182
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:04,360
the confidential documents lost in the accident that only the Emperor,

183
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:05,360
the Prime Minister, and the Army and Navy leaders

184
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:06,690
are allowed to possess.

185
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:09,680
General, are you concerned that this matter

186
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:10,360
might implicate

187
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:12,280
officers from our Sixth Air Base?

188
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:15,720
As you know,

189
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:18,380
the Navy and Army have been constantly feuding.

190
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:20,560
General Ōsumi

191
00:12:20,560 --> 00:12:23,640
had already narrowly escaped several assassination attempts.

192
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,880
Why did this time

193
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:27,340
it happen specifically in my jurisdiction?

194
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,160
Sir,

195
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:30,680
please don't worry too much.

196
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,280
It might simply be an accident

197
00:12:34,040 --> 00:12:35,700
that has nothing to do with us.

198
00:12:37,640 --> 00:12:38,920
We can't rule out that it was done by those

199
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:41,180
hot-headed radicals under our command.

200
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:43,320
If the Major discovers any connection to us

201
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:44,780
and places the blame on us,

202
00:12:46,080 --> 00:12:48,160
I'll become the target of everyone's arrows.

203
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:49,200
Our Sixth Air Base

204
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,260
won't enjoy peace and quiet anymore.

205
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:58,280
While we assist the Major in his investigation,

206
00:12:58,920 --> 00:13:01,450
we must also gather necessary intelligence.

207
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:03,770
During his time on this island,

208
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:06,040
we need to be extra cautious.

209
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:18,060
This is where the doctor sits.

210
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,260
Have a seat.

211
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:26,450
Please sit down.

212
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:31,900
Hold tight.

213
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:36,680
Hold on tight.

214
00:13:58,440 --> 00:13:59,160
Biying.

215
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:01,680
Biying.

216
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:07,000
Hello.

217
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,520
My name is Wumu Yilang.

218
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:10,120
Nice to meet you.

219
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:12,930
I'm here to drop off Biying's luggage.

220
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:15,720
Please come in.

221
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:31,120
Yingying.

222
00:14:33,240 --> 00:14:34,120
What are you doing here?

223
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,440
I brought your luggage back.

224
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:37,040
I just calmed my father down.

225
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:38,080
And now you're here making trouble.

226
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:38,880
Who's here?

227
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:41,080
Master.

228
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,400
You need to come with me.

229
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,160
Hurry up.

230
00:14:43,160 --> 00:14:43,690
- Go.
- Go.

231
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:47,440
Mr. Ye.

232
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:52,050
What are you doing here?

233
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:54,580
I brought Biying's luggage back.

234
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:55,610
Put it there.

235
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:57,200
You may leave now.

236
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:57,920
Mr. Ye,

237
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,640
I'm sorry for the disturbance today.

238
00:15:01,640 --> 00:15:02,720
Please accept my apologies.

239
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:05,160
Your country's soldiers always act this way,

240
00:15:05,160 --> 00:15:07,240
with complete disregard for justice and morality.

241
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:07,760
Vulgar

242
00:15:08,520 --> 00:15:09,200
and reckless.

243
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,400
You're right, Mr. Ye.

244
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:12,200
Some soldiers indeed

245
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,960
behave in vulgar and reckless ways.

246
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,690
I'm also very angry about this.

247
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:17,520
I heard that you, Mr. Ye,

248
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:19,180
were once a consul in America.

249
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:21,760
You must be well-versed in diplomatic affairs

250
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:23,240
and extremely knowledgeable.

251
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:25,900
I hope to have the opportunity to learn from you.

252
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:28,200
Sipo,

253
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:29,690
show him out.

254
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:30,840
Mr. Ye.

255
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:32,570
I don't want to know who you are.

256
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,560
Our family doesn't want anything to do

257
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:35,880
with you, a Japanese man in uniform,

258
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:36,840
whatsoever.

259
00:15:37,360 --> 00:15:38,960
Stop bothering my daughter.

260
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:39,880
Please leave.

261
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:41,280
But I need to take

262
00:15:41,280 --> 00:15:42,200
Ye Biying out to handle something.

263
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:42,800
Leave now.

264
00:15:43,160 --> 00:15:43,760
Takemuro,

265
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:44,720
please go quickly.

266
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:45,720
I'm not leaving.

267
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:50,160
Father,

268
00:15:50,880 --> 00:15:51,740
how about this:

269
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:52,740
I'll see him out

270
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:54,020
and come back soon.

271
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:54,850
Let's go.

272
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:55,970
Ying'er.

273
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:58,060
Father,

274
00:15:58,160 --> 00:15:59,160
I'll be back soon.

275
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:00,320
Please rest well.

276
00:16:01,840 --> 00:16:02,370
Ying'er.

277
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:07,290
Are you trying to get me killed?

278
00:16:26,480 --> 00:16:27,140
Nurse Tang.

279
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:04,319
What's wrong?

280
00:17:04,440 --> 00:17:05,839
Why are you so flustered?

281
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:07,880
Nothing.

282
00:17:09,160 --> 00:17:11,290
Did something happen at the hospital?

283
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:20,040
I went to the comfort station for routine inspection today.

284
00:17:21,359 --> 00:17:23,000
I saw Huihui.

285
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:24,560
Father.

286
00:17:24,920 --> 00:17:26,119
Can you think of a way?

287
00:17:26,839 --> 00:17:27,800
Why don't we

288
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:28,760
rescue Huihui?

289
